Text.string: Hey, do you hear bloodthirsty screaming?
[battle cry]
[karate noises]
Perfect.

Let me catch you up. A while back we found a map. Led to Vaults all over the Borderlands. Dream come true, right? I didn't realize how big of a target it would make us. We got attacked, and the map was lost. I've been lookin' for it ever since.
This way.
I was so focused on finding the map, I didn't notice that Pandora was changing. The bandit clans used to just murder each other for fun. Now they're all under one banner. A cult.
The Children of the Vault.
Ah. The Children of the Vault.
The Children of the Vault.
The Children of the Vault.
Right. Come on, let's take a look around.
Their leaders are the Calypso Twins, and their followers worship them like gods.
They're convinced the map will lead them to something called the Great Vault—and they've been slaughtering anyone who gets in their way.
We heard a rumor that a bandit clan found an alien artifact in the desert. Could be the map. That's what we're here to find out.
It's the Firehawk!
Locked. Heh... not gonna keep a Siren out, though.
Maybe this Shiv asshole knew more about the map.
Have a look around, Vault Hunter.
Let's see what that Shiv asshole knew about the map. Gonna look around.
What do we have here?
You find anything yet?
Look around. There's gotta be SOME intel here.
Any leads, killer?
Let me know if you find something.
Shiv! The Sun Smasher clan has recovered the Sacred Vault Map. Send our followers to invite the Sun Smashers into our holy family. And hurry... the Twin Gods grow hungry.
The map! I knew it. We have to beat them to the Sun Smashers.
I'll open the gate.
Come on, this way.
The God-Queen wants her head!
I'm gonna set up camp and gather some intel on the Calypsos. Find the Sun Smasher warchief and do whatever it takes to get that map.
I like to know who I'm working with. What made you decide to be a Vault Hunter?
Damn it. That's the Sun Smashers' camp, but it looks like the COV got there first. Don't let them leave with the map, killer.
Hello?! Somebody help me! I would prefer not to die like this!
Okay, this is an excellent prank. We've all had, heh, a great time. Except for me. Please, get me down. Please.
Someone help me! That would be you!
Help!
Get me down!
Save me!
Guys, this is not funny. Much.
You can either help me, or I'm gonna yell at you every fifteen seconds.
I would get YOU down! If—if you were... if you were in trouble...
Yo. Little help?
Shoot me down, will ya? I like to hang, but not like this. Not like this!
Uh, could you shoot the chain? Please? Now, maybe?
Very simple process. You shoot the chain, and gravity will work its magic.
Your gun. Bang bang. Snap. Yay!
Uhh, I would like to not be upside down forever. Could you shoot the chain?
Ghh! Ugh...
Ah, my briefs are... ugh. Whoa, ho-ho, hey, yeah... uh, feet... work... good. Nice to meet you.
There's too many of them! We're doomed. Doomed!
Hey, thanks. If you hadn't come along, I might be dead. So... what're you doin' here?
Mission for the Crimson Raiders. Kinda... top secret. Direct orders from Lilith. Might have to kill you.
I came to see Pandora's legendary half-naked bandits, clearly. Also, I just joined up with Lilith and the Crimson Raiders.
I am on an unending hunt for the glory of... oh, as in right now? I am working with Lilith and the Crimson Raiders.
I'm working with the Crimson Raiders. Lilith sent me to find some nonsense. I assume there's a reward.
You're with the Firehawk? Oh man, I used to run with Lilith back in the day! But y'know, now I'm a bandit warchief! Heh-heh-heh... go Sun Smashers.

I mean, at least I used to be a warchief. Until, y'know, my clan found that stupid alien junk. I warned 'em not to mess with that crap, but what do they do? They tie me up and take it to the Calypso Twins. Not cool, bros.
Well, we should probably get out of here before the COV come back. So... where are Lilith and the Raiders hangin' these days?
Former COV propaganda center. Emphasis on former.
A former COV propaganda center. I beat down every last one of them.
The cult propaganda center nearby. It's our territory now.
Former COV propaganda center. It's, uh, under new management.||I killed 'em all.
Now we're talkin'! C'mon, let's get out of here.
I'll lead the way—even though I'm totally unarmed. Can't let 'em know you're afraid and totally defenseless, bro. Bandit life!
So, you took over that COV propaganda center all by your widdle self?
You know it, tighty-whitey.
I did. Barely broke a sweat.
Yes. They fought like animals. Sick, wounded animals.
They had me outnumbered, twenty-to-one. Bad odds for them.
Abandon the mission! Robots and children first!
I am impressed.
Aw, man. The Children of the Vault totally trashed my camp! Like, that is not where that bloody skull should be! It is completely ruining the vibe!
Those Calypsos won't stop until every bandit on Pandora worships them like gods. Bandits don't need gods! We worship a hot fire and a charred piece of meat! There are rules!
Oh, I know a shortcut! This way.
Nggh!
Hyuh!
Hah!
I'm flying!—I'm not flying.
Pandora's in trouble. I can feel it in my bones. Or maybe that's just the harsh desert wind on my bare sun-dappled chest.
So, you find somethin' better to do? Respect.
Hey, where'd you go? I thought we were hittin' it off!
You find somethin' else to do? No sweat. I can hang. Right here.
I'm over here! Probably forgot. Seems like you did.
Uh... you comin'? Cool, cool.
Vault Hunter! You all right over there?
Ugh, skag central, am I right? Y'know, I'm gonna let you take care of them. Only thing I'm packin' right now is... not somethin' I'm gonna use on a skag.
Yo, bro! Take care of those skags, will ya?
Vault Hunter, heh. I cannot come down until you kill those skags.
Once you kill those skags, I'll come down! Promise!
So... are you gonna shoot those skags or what? How—what are we doing?
Coast is clear! Nice! Let's go meet up with the Firehawk!
More COV! Let's see what you got, recruit.
I'm sure Lilith'll be glad to see me! We're tight, bro. Super tight. Like, bro tight. It's a thing.
Ohh, sweet digs! Fortified, well-ventilated—y'know, throw some bloody skulls up on the walls and you've got yourself a nice cozy place here, friend!
Vaughn? What the hell are you doing here?
Heh-heya, Lilith! Former warchief of the Sun Smashers, reporting for duty! [nervous laughter] Go Crimson Raiders!
Heh, it's good to see you, Vaughn. The Raiders will take all the help we can get. So, Vault Hunter—did you find the map?
Pandora's a dangerous place—that grenade mod will come in handy. You should equip it before we get started. Let me know when you're ready.
Ready to chuck some boom and frag some maniacs.
I'm always looking for new ways to take my enemies apart.
A messy tool of death. I like it.
A little extra boom never hurt anyone... except me targets.
All right.
I'll equip it later.
Perhaps I'll equip it later.
I'll equip it another time.
Maybe I'll equip it later.
It's your funeral.
Nice fighting, killer.
Seems like you guys got this! Good luck! I'm gonna... go hang out in some trash.
So what're we working with here? Well, this place kinda sucks, but it's all we got at the moment. Not the first time the Raiders have had to start from scratch.
It's no Sanctuary... hope Ellie gets that ship working soon.
Well, my old squad is all dead, and Vladof thinks I am, too, so... it's just me and Iron Bear. Mech repairs aren't cheap, and I heard there's treasure in the Vaults. Seemed like the right call.
I made my name beating down gangsters and taking out tyrants. I've won every fight I've ever been in, and I'm looking for a real challenge. Opening a Vault is the ultimate fight, right?
Death calls me across the stars to hunt the living and send them to her. I am her knife, and I must forever hone myself. The Vaults are the ultimate hunt, and so I am here.

Oh, I made my money doin' dirty work for every rich arsehole this end of the galaxy. Figured it was safer to quit before one of 'em decided to pay me with a bullet. So Vault Huntin's my retirement, I guess!
Heh. The Vaults attract all kinds. Just remember, the power inside them is hard to resist. It's up to us to make sure it doesn't end up in the wrong hands. Trust me, I've seen it happen.
All right. We've got a foothold. Maybe things are turning our way. Come on, killer, you're with me.
I'll stand guard!
